          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 182W targets with a thickness of 300-350 ug/cm2",
                "were prepared by sputtering the material onto",
                "80-ug/cm2-thick carbon foils and then covered by",
                "10-ug/cm2-thick carbon layer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PS",
                "SISD",
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The recoiled evaporation residues",
                " (ERs) were separated efficiently by A gas-filled",
                "recoil separator, SHANS (Spectrometer for Heavy Atom",
                "and Nuclear Structure) and collected by three 16-strip",
                "position-sensitive silicon detectors (PSSDs), which",
                "were mounted side by side at the focal plane of the",
                "separator. Each PSSD has an active area of 50 X 50 mm2.",
                "The typical energy resolution for the PSSDs was 35 keV",
                " (FWHM) for 6-9 MeV alpha particles."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Eight side silicon detectors (SSDs) were mounted",
                "in front of the PSSDs in an open box geometry."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " In order to distinguish the alpha-decay events",
                "from the implanted products, two multi-wire",
                "proportional counters were installed upstream from",
                "the PSSDs."
              ]
            }
          ],
